Preheat your #oven to 200°C. In a #small bowl mix the @tomato puree{30%g} with the @sun-dried tomato paste{1%tbsp}. Drain the @mozzarella{1} and tear into small pieces.

Put the @pizza bases{2} on a large #baking tray{}. Use the back of a #spoon to spread the tomato sauce mixture evenly all over the base, leave a 1cm edge. Arrange the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} over the pizza, scatter over the mozzarella evenly.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Spoon over the @onion marmalade{40%g} in small dollops.

Bake the pizzas on the top shelf of your #oven until the cheese is melted and bubbly and the base is crisp, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, combine the @olive oil{1%tbsp} with the @balsamic vinegar{12%g} in a #medium sized bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix together, set aside.

Do any washing up whilst you're waiting.

Once the pizza is cooked, add the @wild rocket{40%g} to the salad dressing and toss together. Serve the pizza with the rocket on the side. Enjoy!